Who is your Valentine?

Saint Valentine’s Day, commonly shortened to Valentine’s Day, is an annual commemoration 
held on February 14, celebrating love and affection between intimate companions. 
The day is named after one or more early Christian martyrs, Saint Valentine 
and was established by Pope Gelasius I in 500 AD.
Celebrate this old, traditional holiday, with someone, who’s really special to you.

HAPPY VALENTINE’S DAY!


